      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test specimens from production lots; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to drawing tolerances; specimens span expected manufacturing variability.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production hardware. Dimensional inspection of all screws and rods confirmed conformance to drawing tolerances. Specimens sourced from two production lots to capture manufacturing variability. Sample size consistent with ASTM F1717 guidance. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing performed at multiple clinically relevant loading rates and environmental conditions (ambient and simulated physiological); inter-laboratory reproducibility demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "All testing performed at a single quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min) under ambient laboratory conditions per ASTM F1717. No wet or elevated-temperature conditions tested. Inter-laboratory reproducibility confirmed across two test sites (CV <5% for all QoIs), but the single loading condition limits factor achievement. Gradation 1 achieved; below required Gradation 2. Noted as accepted residual gap given the scope of this submission.",
      "factorNote": "This factor is below required level. Gap accepted by the credibility assessment team given the deterministic nature of the F1717 protocol and the regulatory precedent for ambient testing."
    },
    {
