      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions, preloads) traceable to the same hardware and test conditions used in experimental validation; discrepancies quantified.",
      "rationale": "Model geometry derived from CMM measurements of the same production lot used in testing. Material properties from coupon specimens cut from the same rod stock. Assembly torque replicated in model via bolt pretension elements. Boundary conditions (fixed distal block, load applied at proximal block centroid) match test fixture kinematics. No unresolved equivalency discrepancies. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
