      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) computed for each QoI; all E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10% for mean predictions.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for stiffness (0.81), yield force (0.73), and force at 40 mm (1.12). All three below the 1.96 threshold. Percent differences of 2.4%, 2.0%, and 2.9% respectively, all below the 10% acceptance bound. Validation uncertainty (uval) accounts for experimental measurement uncertainty, model parameter uncertainty, and numerical error. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
