      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements for pedicle screw constructs.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness relates to load sharing with the spine; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement are ASTM F1717 reportable quantities used by FDA to assess structural adequacy. All three QoIs appear in the predicate device 510(k) submissions reviewed. Direct clinical and regulatory relevance established. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
