    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2; the gap is accepted given the deterministic nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol and consistent inter-laboratory reproducibility. All three QoIs satisfy the quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is assessed as credible for the stated COU at Medium assurance level.",
